ge. From then on he, his son (also called James), and his grandson Charles (‘Bonnie Prince Charlie’) made various unsuccessful attempts to recover the English throne. Their supporters were known as Jacobites (from Latin <i>Iacobus</i>), and the name James became for a while particularly associated with Roman Catholicism on the one hand, and Highland opposition to the English government on the other. Nevertheless, it has since become one of the most perennially popular boys' names."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"James Hore was born in 1350. He had at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1350–":"1350–Surnud","1361–Female":"1361–Surnud","1350–Male":"1350–Surnud","1350":"1350","1361":"1361"},"fi":{"1350–":"1350–Kuollut","1361–Female":"1361–Kuollut","1350–Male":"1350–Kuollut","1350":"1350","1361":"1361"},"fr":{"1350–":"1350–Décédé","1361–Female":"1361–Décédée","1350–Male":"1350–Décédé","1350":"1350","1361":"1361","lifeSummary":"James Hore est né en 1350. Il a eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"1350–":"1350–Verstorben","1361–Female":"1361–Verstorben","1350–Male":"1350–Verstorben","1350":"1350","1361":"1361","lifeSummary":"James Hore wurde 1350 geboren. Er hatte mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"1350–":"1350–Desede","1361–Female":"1361–Desede","1350–Male":"1350–Desede","1350":"1350","1361":"1361"},"hu":{"1350–":"1350–elhunyt","1361–Female":"1361–elhunyt","1350–Male":"1350–elhunyt","1350":"1350","1361":"1361"},"id":{"1350–":"1350–Telah Meninggal","1361–Female":"1361–Telah Meninggal","1350–Male":"1350–Telah Meninggal","1350":"1350","1361":"1361"},"it":{"1350–":"1350–Deceduto","1361–Female":"1361–Deceduta","1350–Male":"1350–Deceduto","1350":"1350","1361":"1361","lifeSummary":"James Hore è nato il nel 1350. Lui avuto almeno 1 figlia."},"ja":{"1350–":"1350年–死亡","1361–Female":"1361年–死亡","1350–Male":"1350年–死亡","1350":"1350年","1361":"1361年","lifeSummary":"James Horeは1350年に生まれた。彼は少なくとも1人の娘をもうけた。"},"ko":{"1350–":"1350년–사망","1361–Female":"1361년–사망","1350–Male":"1350년–사망","1350":"1350년","1361":"1361년